i only confess on days
when it's raining
i'm sure it's raining somewhere

my lips are sin stained
i wear shame like a holey sweater

i only wanted to dream with you
to lie under your arm
tucked in your hip
night passing while we whispered
tomorrow's into the darkness

i only wanted you to absolve me
of the years i spent not staring
into your eyes while hail mary's
coated my tongue like bitter medicine

i don't mean to live in this hallucinatory place never
quite in focus
where love doesn't need to be earned
where i am always deemed worthy
of the joy i have been afraid to name

i confess I only wanted to
dream with you
while the rain beat the windows
and your arm covered my chest
warming the very place i keep my sins

